<subSubSection id="C31C6528A4661877FF67FDD9D59EFD59" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB936A3A4661877FF67FDD9D570FD71" blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B972EAB1A4661877FF67FDD9D744FDA1" bold="true" box="[198,358,557,583]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Recognition:</emphasis>
The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D20A4661877FDECFDD9D522FDA0" box="[589,768,557,582]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAB1A4661877FDECFDD9D522FDA0" box="[589,768,557,582]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Porphyrochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the following hypothesized synapomorphies: 
<number id="3DCE2484A4661877FF36FDA1D686FD89" box="[151,164,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
) male tergite 
<number id="3DCE2484A4661877FEEAFDA1D778FD89" box="[331,346,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="8.0">8</number>
with only a few setae confined posterolaterally; 
<number id="3DCE2484A4661877FC3CFDA1D58FFD89" box="[925,941,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
) male tergite 
<number id="3DCE2484A4661877FBF0FDA1D27DFD89" box="[1105,1119,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="7.0">7</number>
with posteroventral protuberances; 
<number id="3DCE2484A4661877FEACFD89D73EFD71" box="[269,284,637,663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
) abdomen metallic blue or blue-green in colour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936A3A4661877FF67FD51D59EFD59" blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" box="[198,956,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B972EAB1A4661877FF67FD51D743FD59" bold="true" box="[198,353,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Description:</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B52A4661877FE3BFD51D4C8FD59" author="Rafael" box="[410,746,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2004) The Neotropical genera Macrostomus Wiedemann and Porphyrochroa Melander (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 21 (3), 439 - 448." type="journal article" year="2004">
Rafael and Cumming (
<number id="3DCE2484A4661877FD05FD51D4C0FD59" box="[676,738,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for redescription.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C6528A4661877FF67FD39D7E3FCD1" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB936A3A4661877FF67FD39D7E3FCD1" blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B972EAB1A4661877FF67FD39D760FD01" bold="true" box="[198,322,717,743]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks:</emphasis>
The precise sister-group of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D20A4661877FD61FD39D57CFD00" box="[704,862,717,742]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAB1A4661877FD61FD39D57CFD00" box="[704,862,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Macrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D20A4661877FCDCFD39D20CFD00" box="[893,1070,717,742]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAB1A4661877FCDCFD39D20CFD00" box="[893,1070,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Porphyrochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
